page.title: 12Green Lane.
page.content: Green Lane is a track leading off from Fen Lane.It has fields on either side of it,mostly with barley growing in them.There is a variety of plants growing at the side of the track,including Meadow Fescue and Colt's Foot.The area is alive with the sound of birds.Partridges, sparrows,blackbirds,great tits and thrushes have regularly been seen. The track is a public right of way,though it remains untarred and rutted.It is dusty after dry spells,though heavy rain causes the formation of numerous puddles.
